In this study, Ni–Co–MoS2 nanoboxes was found to exhibit superior peroxidase catalytic activity. In addition of GLY in sensing system, to inhibit the oxidation process of TMB and diminished blue colour (Fig. 5). The concentrations of GLY ranged from 0 μM to 50 μM, the gradual decrease in absorption intensity and no lower peaks were observed at higher concentrations (Fig. 6
                        a). A linear graph representing the addition of GLY is shown in Fig. 6b, enabling easy calculation of the limit of detection using the formula 3SD/s. The limit of detection for GLY was determined to be 3 nM, which is lower than that of some previously reported nanozymes (Table 1
                        ). To evaluate the selectivity of this colorimetric sensor, other organophosphorus pesticides and common ions were introduced into the system. The results, presented in Fig. 6c, demonstrate a significant increase in absorption intensity for other organophosphorus pesticides and common ions compared to GLY. These findings indicate that the presence of various interferences does not impact GLY detection, highlighting the excellent selectivity of the colorimetric assay for GLY.
